column9: My National service year (NYSC) ends this September and I plan to fully settle down here in Abuja. My leave starts two weeks after the official end date  because I plan to get a house of my own before I travel home. I may not have the chance to see my family this Christmas. I'm well aware that a lot of people would apply for leave at that time so this may be my only chance to go sort out everything I need to at home. I have been falling ill constantly so I need to see my family Doctor and have myself treated properly before my return to Abuja. My father's birthday celebration is around that time and I need to be there to help with the celebrations. That is just two of the many things on my list.  In summary, I have a lot to do back home in Port-Harcourt and this may be the only chance I would get for a very long time. Post NYSC spells the start of a new phase of my life so I want to get away for a bit, get refreshed and come back to do my best work.
